  "description": "When Elizabeth Povinelli published Geontologies: A Requiem to Late Liberalism (2016ce), she introduced a vocabulary for analyzing how late liberalism organizes the divide between Life and Nonlife. That distinction (life as vitality, nonlife as inert background) is a great lens for looking at Flavor Town as a commercial brand and imaginary space.\nDiners, Drive-Ins, and Dives continually codes flame, sizzle, and \u0026ldquo;the money bite\u0026rdquo; as the pulse of Life, while the petroleum-and-broadcast infrastructure is folded down into a silent Nonlife substrate.\n",
